# BROWSER-core.md - Twitter/X Global Rules & Shared Patterns


## Selectors

| Element | Selector |
|---------|----------|
| Tweet article | `article[data-testid="tweet"]` |
| User name | `[data-testid="User-Name"]` |
| Tweet text | `[data-testid="tweetText"]` |
| Tweet link | `a[href*="/status/"]` |
| Reply button | `[data-testid="reply"]` |
| Like button | `[data-testid="like"]` → `[data-testid="unlike"]` when liked |
| Retweet button | `[data-testid="retweet"]` |
| Views | `a[href*="/analytics"] span` |
| Textarea (reply) | `[data-testid="tweetTextarea_0"]` |
| Textarea (dialog) | `[role="dialog"] [data-testid="tweetTextarea_0"]` |
| Submit button (reply) | `[data-testid="tweetButtonInline"]` |
| Submit button (dialog) | `[role="dialog"] [data-testid="tweetButton"]` |
| Follow button | `[data-testid$="-follow"]` (text "Follow"/"Follow Back") |
| Compose | `a[href="/compose/tweet"]` or `[data-testid="SideNav_NewTweet_Button"]` |

## § 1 — Typing (clipboard paste)

**For replies (on tweet page) — ONE evaluate call: paste + submit:**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var ta = document.querySelector('[data-testid=\"tweetTextarea_0\"]'); if (!ta) return { error: 'no textarea' }; ta.focus(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); var dt = new DataTransfer(); dt.setData('text/plain', window.__data.text); ta.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', { clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); var typed = ta.innerText.trim(); if (!typed) return { error: 'paste failed' }; var btn = document.querySelector('[data-testid=\"tweetButtonInline\"]'); if (!btn || btn.disabled) return { error: 'button disabled', text: typed.slice(0, 80) }; btn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); return { posted: true, text: typed.slice(0, 80) }; }", "data": {"text": "YOUR_REPLY_HERE"}}
ENDJSON
```

**For compose dialog (original tweet, quote tweet):**

**Full flow (ONE evaluate — clear + paste + submit):**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var ta = document.querySelector('[role=\"dialog\"] [data-testid=\"tweetTextarea_0\"]'); if (!ta) return { error: 'no textarea' }; ta.focus(); document.execCommand('selectAll'); document.execCommand('delete'); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); var text = window.__data.text; var dt = new DataTransfer(); dt.setData('text/html', text.replace(/\\n/g, '<br>')); dt.setData('text/plain', text); ta.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', { clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var btn = document.querySelector('[role=\"dialog\"] [data-testid=\"tweetButton\"]'); if (!btn || btn.disabled) return { error: 'button disabled', text: ta.innerText.slice(0, 100) }; btn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); return { posted: !document.querySelector('[role=\"dialog\"]'), len: text.length }; }", "data": {"text": "YOUR_TWEET_HERE"}}
ENDJSON
```

**Format rules for original tweets:**
- Hook line first (standalone, punchy)
- Blank line between sections (`\n\n`)
- Body lines: text-based bullets (→, -, •)
- @mentions typed as text (auto-linked by Twitter)
- Hashtags on last line (3 max)
## § 5 — Like + Read + Dedup (combined — ONE evaluate on post page)

After navigating to a tweet page, this single evaluate likes the tweet, reads its full text, detects media, and checks if we already replied.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var articles = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[data-testid=\"tweet\"]')); var target = articles[0]; if (!target) return { error: 'no article' }; var text = (target.querySelector('[data-testid=\"tweetText\"]') || {}).innerText || ''; var hasMedia = !!target.querySelector('[data-testid=\"tweetPhoto\"]') || !!target.querySelector('[data-testid=\"videoPlayer\"]'); var likeBtn = target.querySelector('[data-testid=\"like\"]'); if (likeBtn) likeBtn.click(); var alreadyLiked = !!target.querySelector('[data-testid=\"unlike\"]'); var alreadyReplied = articles.some(function(a) { var user = a.querySelector('[data-testid=\"User-Name\"]'); return user && user.innerText.includes('@{{handle_slug}}'); }); return { text: text.slice(0, 300), hasMedia: hasMedia, liked: !!likeBtn, alreadyLiked: alreadyLiked, alreadyReplied: alreadyReplied }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

- `alreadyReplied: true` → track + skip
- `hasMedia && text.length < 80` → likely meme/image post, skip (can't see image)
- `alreadyLiked: true` → already liked, no action needed

To like a specific tweet on a feed/search page (without the combined read):
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { const tweets = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[data-testid=\"tweet\"]')); const target = tweets.find(t => { const link = t.querySelector('a[href*=\"/status/\"]'); return link?.getAttribute('href')?.includes('/' + window.__data.tweetId); }); if (!target) return { error: 'tweet not found' }; const likeBtn = target.querySelector('[data-testid=\"like\"]'); if (!likeBtn) { if (target.querySelector('[data-testid=\"unlike\"]')) return { already_liked: true }; return { error: 'like button not found' }; } likeBtn.click(); return { clicked: true }; }", "data": {"tweetId": "TWEET_ID"}}
ENDJSON
```
